We recommended that Management through the Human Resource Department and Accounting Office:
To see to it that monthly net take-home pay of employees shall not be less than ₱5,000. In the event that total authorized deductions shall reduce net take home pay to ₱5,000, deductions shall be made in accordance with the order of preference under Section 55 of the General Provisions of the 2022 GAA;
Through the HRMO to consider implementing financial wellness programs to assist them. These programs could include financial counseling or education, debt management advice, or even assistance with consolidating or refinancing loans, or provision of resources and information about financial planning and budgeting;
Through the HRMO to also consider negotiating with the financial institutions that provide the loans to their employees. Management  can try to secure more favorable loan terms, such as lower interest rates or longer repayment periods, which would result in lower loan payments and higher take-home pay for the employees and;
To implement caps on loan amounts or limiting the number of loans an employee can take out at once, to prevent employees from taking on more debt than they can handle.

